text: ==Current Roster== Season 2018-2019 Coach: Octavian {| class="wikitable sortable" !Jersey No. !Name !Date Birth !Height !Position !Country |- |1 |Selly Nurfauziah |19-Des-2002 |158 |Opposite Hitter | |- |2 |Rika Novanti |2-Nov-1997 |158 |Libero | |- |3 |Maulida Auliya Nisa |15-Jun-1999 |172 |Opposite Hitter | |- |6 |Tanti Triana |27-Jan-1996 |170 |Setter | |- |7 |Ratri Wulandari |6-Mei-2002 |177 |Outside hitter | |- |8 |Lissa B Surusa | |170 |Opposite Hitter | |- |9 |Anastasia Regina Putri | |175 |Middle Blocker | |- |10 |Jutarat Montripila |2-Oct-1986 |175 |Opposite Hitter | |- |11 |Maya Kurnia Indri | |178 |Middle Blocker | |- |12 |Chika Swinerlin Pratiwi | |159 |Libero | |- |14 |Alya Anastasya | |177 |Outside hitter | |- |16 |Mita Chantika | |175 |Opposite Hitter | |- |16 |Savira Dwi Oktaviani | |162 |Setter | |- |17 |Sinta Adila | |173 |Middle Blocker | |} Jakarta Elektrik PLN is an Indonesian women's volleyball club owned and managed by the Perusahaan Listrik Negara that plays at the Proliga. ==History== The first championship won by the club was in 2004 and the next year, the club was the runner-up. In 2009 and 2011 the club won again the championship, having won the silver medal in 2008, 2010 and 2012. The next championships were in 2015 and 2016. The club participated at the 2016 Asian Women's Club Volleyball Championship. ==Honours== :Proliga :*Champions (3): 2011, 2015, 2016 :*Runners-up (2): 2010, 2012 ==References== Category:Indonesian volleyball clubs Category:Volleyball clubs established in 2004
